🥗 Project Title: MealMaster (Dietary Management App)
Summary: MealMaster is a modern, responsive web application built to streamline personal nutrition management. It bridges the gap between complex health data and user-friendly tracking, allowing users to calculate their metabolic needs and log daily meals in real-time.

The Live Experience: You can view the fully functional deployment here: 👉 MealMaster Live Demo-https://gilded-chaja-11a5c3.netlify.app

🌟 Core Functionalities
Smart Macro Calculation: Automatically determines target protein, carbohydrate, and fat intake based on user-specific metrics.
Intuitive Meal Logging: A categorized interface for Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, and Snacks to keep daily records organized.
Dynamic Calorie Budgeting: Real-time updates that show calories remaining versus calories consumed.
Responsive UI: A mobile-first design philosophy ensuring the app works perfectly on phones, tablets, and desktops.

💻 Technical Architecture
I built this project with a focus on performance and clean state management:
Framework: React.js (utilizing Vite for optimized bundling)
Styling: Tailwind CSS (for a modern, utility-first design system)
Deployment: Integrated with Netlify for automated CI/CD pipelines.

🛠️ How to Run This Locally
Clone the repository using git clone.
Navigate to the folder and run npm install to grab the dependencies.
Use npm run dev to launch the local development environment.
Open localhost:5173 in your browser.

📖 Why I Built This
This project was born out of a need for a clutter-free diet tracker. Many existing apps are overwhelmed with ads and complex menus; MealMaster focuses on speed and essential data visualization to help users stay consistent with their health goals.
